If the output starts looking too locked, too static, too dot-driven, or too far from the source images, I would tune in this order:

//
Lower LTX Director Motion Brush V2 Guide Attention first.
This is specifically the “how much still-image Director guidance competes with motion IC-LoRA” knob.

//
Lower LTXAddVideoICLoRAGuide strength if the motion-track data overpower the video (they will appear transposed over top of the video).

//
Leave LTXICLoRALoaderModelOnly strength_model near 1 unless you intentionally want the LoRA itself weaker.
